## Limitations

The findings are based on available online resources and may not encompass all aspects of body language in communication. The interpretation of body language can vary across different cultures and contexts, which may not be fully addressed in the sources reviewed. Additionally, the lack of empirical studies in the sources limits the ability to generalize the findings universally. Further research, including cross-cultural studies and empirical investigations, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the role of body language in communication.

